Patriotic Russians have fundraised money for everything from rifle scopes to boots for soldiers, all of which have been sent to Ukraine. Reports have emerged of Russian troops being resupplied with Soviet-era field telephones rather than modern weapons and Ukrainian soldiers often out-arm their opponents because of the advanced weaponry sent to them by Western allies. Sophia, who volunteers in a crowdfunding programme, told The Telegraph the success of the fundraising campaign shows that people are supporting Putin's war. She said: "The money comes in from all over the country,” she said. “Somebody might send 100 roubles (£1.26) and somebody else might send 100,000 roubles, it all helps.” FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 